:Namespace SmokeTest

‚ćĚ Drives a real background server process against a temp fixture folder,
‚ćĚ over HTTP, using HttpCommand rather than an in-process call - the one
‚ćĚ path that exercises Initialize's $APL_SERVICE_APP_CONFIG override (a
‚ćĚ running interpreter cannot set its own environment variables, so that
‚ćĚ branch is untestable in-process; see InitializeTests) and the real
‚ćĚ Jarvis/Conga request-handling path end to end. A live HTTP round trip
‚ćĚ against this server is empirically flaky in some environments (an
‚ćĚ occasional bare 500 from Conga before the request reaches any
‚ćĚ application code, confirmed unrelated to Get/BuildListingResponse by
‚ćĚ direct instrumentation): GetWithRetries absorbs both server start-up
‚ćĚ latency and that transient failure mode.

    ‚ąá d‚ÜźTempDir
      d‚Üź2 ‚éēNQ'.' 'GetEnvironment' 'TMPDIR'
      :If 0‚ąä‚ćīd ‚čĄ d‚Üź'/tmp' ‚čĄ :EndIf
      :If '/'‚Č†¬Į1‚ÜĎd ‚čĄ d‚Üźd,'/' ‚čĄ :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá dir‚ÜźFreshDir name
    ‚ćĚ An empty temp directory, removing any leftover from a prior run.
      dir‚Üź(TempDir),name
      :Trap 0 ‚čĄ 3 ‚éēNDELETE dir ‚čĄ :Else ‚čĄ :EndTrap
      ‚éēMKDIR dir
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá root‚ÜźDyalogRoot
    ‚ćĚ Same derivation Jarvis itself uses (vendor/jarvis/Jarvis.dyalog), so
    ‚ćĚ HttpCommand is found the same way regardless of install location.
      root‚Üź{‚ćĶ,('/\'‚ąä‚ć®‚äĘ/‚ćĶ)‚Üď'/'}{0‚ąä‚ćīt‚Üź2 ‚éēNQ'.' 'GetEnvironment' 'DYALOG':‚äÉ1 ‚éēNPARTS‚äÉ2 ‚éēNQ'.' 'GetCommandLineArgs' ‚čĄ t}''
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá LoadHttpCommand
      :If 0=#.‚éēNC'HttpCommand'
          ‚éēFIX'file://',DyalogRoot,'Library/Conga/HttpCommand.dyalog'
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (rc resp)‚ÜźGetWithRetries url;attempt
      LoadHttpCommand
      :For attempt :In ‚ć≥10
          :Trap 0
              resp‚ÜźHttpCommand.Get url
              :If 200=resp.HttpStatus
                  rc‚Üź0
                  ‚Üí0
              :EndIf
          :EndTrap
          ‚éēDL 1
      :EndFor
      rc‚Üź1
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá StopServer
    ‚ćĚ Kills both the dyalogscript wrapper and the dyalog interpreter it
    ‚ćĚ execs as a child (confirmed empirically: killing only the wrapper's
    ‚ćĚ own PID leaves the interpreter running as an orphan, still bound to
    ‚ćĚ the port). -9 is required: a plain SIGTERM left the interpreter
    ‚ćĚ running, also confirmed empirically. Matches on the launcher
    ‚ćĚ script's own name, which is unique enough for a smoke test that
    ‚ćĚ never runs two servers at once.
      {}‚éēSH'pkill -9 -f ''start-server\.apls'' 2>/dev/null'
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźTest_SmokeTestFilesEndpointReturnsFixtureContents;root;cfgDir;cfgPath;logPath;rc;resp;body;file
      root‚ÜźFreshDir'apl-service-e2e-root'
      (‚äā'x')‚éēNPUT(root,'/photo.jpg')1
      cfgDir‚ÜźFreshDir'apl-service-e2e-config'
      cfgPath‚ÜźcfgDir,'/app.config.json'
      (‚äā'{"rootFolder": "',root,'"}')‚éēNPUT cfgPath 1
      logPath‚Üź(TempDir),'apl-service-e2e-server.log'

      {}‚éēSH'cd ',#.RepoRoot,' && APL_SERVICE_APP_CONFIG=',cfgPath,' dyalogscript apl-service/scripts/start-server.apls >',logPath,' 2>&1 &'
      (rc resp)‚ÜźGetWithRetries'http://127.0.0.1:8080/files'
      StopServer

      :If rc‚Č†0
          r‚Üź0
      :Else
          body‚Üź‚éēJSON resp.Data
          file‚Üź‚äÉbody.files
          r‚Üź(body.folder‚Č°root)‚ąß(1=‚ČĘbody.files)‚ąß(file.fileName‚Č°'photo.jpg')‚ąß(file.type‚Č°'image')
      :EndIf

      3 ‚éēNDELETE root
      3 ‚éēNDELETE cfgDir
    ‚ąá

:EndNamespace
